  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Put a large <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add the <strong>dried yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675780916809-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675780916809-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675780916809-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675780916809-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675780916809-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the pan, then reduce the heat to low</p><p>Cook for 8-10 min or until the onion has softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675780925560-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675780925560-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675780925560-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675780925560-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675780925560-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, peel and chop (or grate!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>soft cheese </strong>in a separate bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!), a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Stir it all together – this is your <strong>white sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675780937590-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675780937590-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675780937590-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675780937590-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675780937590-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pizza base mix</strong> to the bowl with the yeast mixture</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the <strong>dough ball</strong> out onto a<strong> </strong>floured work surface and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span></p><p>Toss each <strong>dough ball</strong> in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
